			<CASNumber>10043-52-4</CASNumber>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Calcium chloride is a chemical compound that is typically produced through the reaction of limestone (calcium carbonate) with hydrochloric acid. It is a salt and is used for various purposes including as a de-icing agent, in food processing, in the oil industry, and as a desiccant. Its product flow can include extraction of raw materials, chemical synthesis, packaging, distribution, usage, and disposal or recycling. The quality of the calcium chloride, its compliance with standards, and its usage information are part of its commercial specification. It is available commercially as a pure substance or as part of various commercial formulations, and can be delivered to consumers or available at the plant for industrial use.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">氯化钙是一种化学化合物，通常通过石灰石（碳酸钙）与盐酸发生反应制得。它是一种盐类，用途广泛，包括作为除冰剂、食品加工、油产业以及作为干燥剂。其产品流程可能包括原材料的提取、化学合成、包装、分销、使用以及废弃物处理或回收。氯化钙的质量、标准合规性和使用信息是其商业规格的一部分。它以纯净物质的形式或作为不同商业制剂的一部分，在商业上出售，可以交付给消费者或在工厂中供工业使用。</common:generalComment>
